{{Infobox power station | name = Eidsfossen Power Station | name_official = ''Eidsfossen kraftverk'' | image = Eidsfossen kraftverk (Tynset).JPG | location_map = Hedmark | location_map_caption = Location in [[Hedmark]] county | coordinates = {{coord|62|31|17|N|10|22|42|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Tynset]], [[Hedmark]] | country = Norway | owner = [[Kraftverkene i Orkla|KVO]] | status = D | commissioned = 1917 | decommissioned = 1999 | psps_upper_res = | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = | psps_generators = | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 0.7 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Eidsfossen Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Eidsfossen kraftverk}}<ref name="Kvikne1">{{cite web |title=Eidsfossen |url=http://www.kvikne.com/Attraksjoner/Eidsfossen.aspx |website=Kvikne i storbukkens rike |accessdate=July 24, 2018}}</ref> or ''Eidsfossen kraftstasjon''<ref name="Kvikne2">{{cite web |title=Eidsfossen kraftverk |url=http://www.kvikne.no/OmKvikne/Eidsfossen.aspx |website=Kvikne.no |accessdate=July 24, 2018}}</ref><ref name="Yr">{{cite web |title=Eidsfossen kraftstasjon, Tynset (Hedmark) |url=https://www.yr.no/sted/Norge/Hedmark/Tynset/Eidsfossen_kraftstasjon/ |website=Yr |publisher=NRK and Meteorologisk institutt |accessdate=July 24, 2018}}</ref>) is a decommissioned [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in the municipality of [[Tynset]] in [[Hedmark]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref name="Yr"/>
The power station is located in the Kvikne Forest (''Kvikneskogen''). It utilized a drop of {{convert|48|m|sp=us}} on the [[Orkla (river)|Orkla River]]. The power plant was built to supply electricity to the [[Røstvangen Mines]] and built from 1915 to 1917, when it became operational.<ref name="Kvikne1"/><ref name="Kvikne2"/> The plant was decommissioned in 1999.<ref name="Kvikne2"/>
An information sign about the power plant has been set up at a [[rest area]] along [[Norwegian National Road 3]], and the old dam construction for the plant can be seen from the same route {{convert|5|km|sp=us}} south of [[Yset]].<ref name="Kvikne1"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Røe |first1=Eirik |title=Ikke imponert over turistattraksjoner |url=https://www.retten.no/lokale-nyheter/ikke-imponert-over-turistattraksjoner/s/1-25-6160172 |accessdate=July 24, 2018 |work=Arbeidets Rett |date=July 23, 2012}}</ref>
