{{primary sources|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = Endeavour Energy | logo = Endeavour energy.png | caption = | type = [[Partnership (Australia)]] | traded_as = | fate = | predecessor = [[Integral Energy]] | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|2011|03|01|df=y}} | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Sydney]] | location_country = Australia | locations = | area_served = Western [[Sydney]], [[Blue Mountains, New South Wales|Blue Mountains]], [[Southern Highlands, New South Wales|Southern Highlands]] and [[Illawarra, New South Wales|Illawarra]] areas of [[New South Wales|NSW]] | key_people = | industry = Electricity | products = | services = [[Electricity distribution]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = Partnership between a consortium led by [[Macquarie Group|Macquarie Infrastructure and Real Assets]] with the [[Government of New South Wales|NSW Government]] | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.endeavourenergy.com.au}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Endeavour Energy''' is the operator of the electrical distribution network for Greater Western [[Sydney, Australia|Sydney]], the [[Blue Mountains (New South Wales)|Blue Mountains]], the [[Southern Highlands (New South Wales)|Southern Highlands]] and the [[Illawarra]] region of NSW, Australia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.endeavourenergy.com.au/wps/portal/ee/!ut/p/a1/lZHJboMwEIZfJTlwBJuw94aqtKjqoiqKGnyJDAzgCGzHmNC-fU2qntp0mcNIM_pm-wcRtEOE0xNrqGaC026OSbjPVkmaXftu8pRka5yub263Yey7m2dsgNwA-IKl-Lf6F0QQKbmWukU5wH6CYmAaLNyK3nhaiFFbeGrFYoIFVTDjkjZQwcAafo5KVqG8cKmfJFVtx1VFbd8tVjat6tIOIjeCxPWCIISPYT-ve4dI04nifHqe8sKLG0QU1KBAOaMy6VZreWVhCzOuFeWgHQA6Dk4perOoHCwshdK0-zxh9t81a8Wg0e5rk5llh-ORpEYYwTW8GuwvyuTmFdFlrT20-adcst_28aGW8ZvXne7rx4d0uXwH3wEoIA!!/dl5/d5/L2dBISEvZ0FBIS9nQSEh/|title=Endeavour Energy - About us|publisher=Endeavour Energy|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref>
==Background== It was formed from the previously state-owned energy retailer/supplier, [[Integral Energy]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.endeavourenergy.com.au/wps/wcm/connect/EE/NSW/NSW+Homepage/aboutUsNav/|title=Endeavour Energy - About us|publisher=Endeavour Energy|accessdate=29 July 2012}}</ref> when the retail division of the company, along with the Integral Energy brand, was sold by the [[Government of New South Wales|NSW Government]] in 2011 to [[Origin Energy]].
On June 2017, an Australian-led consortium of institutional investors acquired 50.4% ownership of the rights to management Endeavour Energy’s network assets under a 99-year lease.
The consortium is led by Macquarie Infrastructure and Real Assets (MIRA), and includes AMP Capital, British Columbia Investment Management Corporation and Qatar Investment Authority.
The NSW Government retains a 49.6% interest and continues to regulate safety and reliability.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.endeavourenergy.com.au/wps/portal/ee/!ut/p/a1/lZHJboMwEIZfJTlwBJuw94aqtKjqoiqKGnyJDAzgCGzHmNC-fU2qntp0mcNIM_pm-wcRtEOE0xNrqGaC026OSbjPVkmaXftu8pRka5yub263Yey7m2dsgNwA-IKl-Lf6F0QQKbmWukU5wH6CYmAaLNyK3nhaiFFbeGrFYoIFVTDjkjZQwcAafo5KVqG8cKmfJFVtx1VFbd8tVjat6tIOIjeCxPWCIISPYT-ve4dI04nifHqe8sKLG0QU1KBAOaMy6VZreWVhCzOuFeWgHQA6Dk4perOoHCwshdK0-zxh9t81a8Wg0e5rk5llh-ORpEYYwTW8GuwvyuTmFdFlrT20-adcst_28aGW8ZvXne7rx4d0uXwH3wEoIA!!/dl5/d5/L2dBISEvZ0FBIS9nQSEh/|title=Endeavour Energy - About us|publisher=Endeavour Energy|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.treasury.nsw.gov.au/projects-initiatives/commercial-transactions/past-projects|title=The Treasury - Past projects|publisher=The Treasury NSW Government|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref>
