{{Infobox power station | name = Hitra Wind Farm | name_official = Hitra vindpark | image = StraumHitra.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = View of the farm on top of the mountain | image_alt = | location_map = Trøndelag#Norway | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = Location of the park | coordinates = {{coord|63|32|31|N|08|45|32|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Norway | location = [[Hitra]], [[Trøndelag]] | status = O | construction_began = July 2003 | commissioned = {{Start date|2004|10|14}} | decommissioned = | cost = {{NOK|450 million|link=yes}} | owner = [[Statkraft]] | operator = | wind_farm_type = Onshore | wind_site_elevation = {{Convert|300|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | wind_site_usage = Mountain plateau | wind_site_area = | wind_hub_height = {{Convert|70|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | wind_rotor_diameter = {{Convert|82.4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | wind_rated_speed = | ps_units_operational = 24 x 2.3&nbsp;MW | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_electrical_capacity = 55.2 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 31.0%<!-- 150,000 MWh/year / ( 55.2 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.310 --> | ps_annual_generation = 150 | website = | extra = Source<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statkraft.no/Images/Hitra+Faktaark+2_tcm3-5923.pdf|title=Hitra vindpark|author=[[Statkraft]]|language=Norwegian|format=PDF|accessdate=2010-12-28}}</ref> }}
'''Hitra Wind Farm''' is a 24-turbine [[wind farm]] located in the municipality of [[Hitra]] in [[Trøndelag]] county, [[Norway]] and operated by [[Statkraft]]. The farm is located on top of the Elsfjellet plateau in the central part of the [[Hitra (island)|island of Hitra]], just {{convert|3|km}} south of the village of Straum and about {{convert|15|km}} west of [[Sandstad]]. Until the expansion of the [[Smøla Wind Farm]] in 2005, Hitra was the largest wind farm in the country and had total cost of {{NOK|450 million|link=yes}}.
Each of the 24 [[wind turbine]]s can produce {{convert|2.3|MW|lk=on}} of power for a maximum generated power of {{convert|55|MW}} and an annual production of {{convert|150|GWh|lk=on}} for the whole farm. The farm was opened on 14 October 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statkraft.no/pub/vindkraft/vindparker/hitra/index.asp|title=Hitra vindpark|author=[[Statkraft]]|accessdate=2007-11-07|language=Norwegian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071106165427/http://statkraft.no/pub/vindkraft/vindparker/hitra/index.asp|archivedate=2007-11-06}}</ref>
The [[Fosen Vind]] {{convert|1|GW|lk=on}} wind farm complex will include the nearby Hitra 2 wind farm.
