{{Infobox power station | name = Perovo Solar Park | name_official = | image = Perovosolarstation.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Crimea | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = Location of the Perovo Solar Park in Crimea | coordinates = {{coord|44|54|N|33|56|E|region:UA_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = | location = Perovo, [[Crimea]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = PV | ps_units_operational = 440,000 | solar_csp_heliostats = | solar_site_area = {{convert|200|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}} {{convert|200|ha|km2|0|abbr=on}} | ps_electrical_capacity = 100 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = 132.5 [[GWh]]<ref>[http://www.mfa.gov.ua/greece/en/news/detail/74089.htm World’s Largest Solar Park in Ukraine]</ref> | website = | extra = }} The '''Perovo Solar Park''' is a 100 MWp [[photovoltaic power station]] located at Perovo, [[Simferopol Raion]], [[Crimea]]. As of July 2012 it is the world's fourth-largest solar farm, and is made up of 440,000&nbsp;[[solar panel]]s. It is owned by [[Activ Solar]], and the final 20 MW stage was completed on December 29, 2011.
In 2009, Ukraine established a [[feed-in tariff]] of €0.46 per kilowatt hour until 2030, one of the highest.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/europe-s-biggest-solar-park-completed-with-russian-bank-debt-1-.html Europe’s Biggest Solar Park Completed With Russian Bank Debt]</ref>
